## Analysis of Main Target Image

The target structure resembles a simple vehicle or cart with the following components:
- 3 layers in total
- 4 building blocks total

Layer 1 (Bottom): Two orange cylindrical blocks positioned horizontally and parallel to each other, serving as wheels/rollers
Layer 2 (Middle): One yellow rectangular block positioned horizontally on top of the orange cylinders, serving as a platform/base
Layer 3 (Top): One blue cubic block positioned on top of the yellow rectangular block, slightly toward the back

Spatial Relationships:
- The two orange cylinders are parallel to each other with a small gap between them
- The yellow rectangular block sits across both orange cylinders
- The blue cube sits on top of the yellow rectangular block, positioned slightly toward one end of the rectangle

## Block Selection from Dictionary

Based on the target image, I need the following blocks:
1. Blue cube - matches block index 1
2. Yellow rectangular block (horizontal orientation) - matches block index 7
3. Two orange cylindrical blocks (horizontal orientation) - matches block index 14 (needed twice)

## Assembly Order

The logical assembly order would be bottom to top:

```
{
    Step1: Move block with index 14
    Step2: Move block with index 14
    Step3: Move block with index 7
    Step4: Move block with index 1
}
```

This will create the cart structure with the orange cylinders as wheels at the bottom, the yellow rectangular block as the platform in the middle, and the blue cube on top.
